rComments: The lectures were poorly prepared. The material covered in class was not too difficult but the professor somehow managed to make some parts of it confusing. Reading the book at home instead of copying it from the blackboard would have been a better investment of my time.

Very badly run/taught course. The assignments were long, tedious and usually tough(half was usually off-topic). As others mention, he seems to discover the material himself at the board while reading butchered notes from the textbook (horrible choice of textbook too). Final exam was easy if prepared: unfair expectations (extreme memorization/fail).

rComments: Asks for a lot of work from students but isn't making any effort himself: wants perfect proofs when most of the time he's not able to copy proofs correctly on the blackboard. In the "Moore method" section, he asks us to prove results he isn't even familiar with.

I never had a teacher so unprepared, he basically discovers the material while copying the book on the board. He gives lots of homework, usually long and boring. His exams aren't easy but not too hard either, it's just frustrating that he asks a lot of you when he's not doing anything. I would recommend to avoid him. Great researcher though

One of the worst professors I have ever had. Made lectures unbearable by blatantly plagiarizing "lecture notes" from the textbook.
